  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Pure depth, no equivocation. Cinder Black is the color you choose when you want the roof to define the silhouette of the house rather than blend into it. On a Florida elevation it absorbs heat aggressively, so attic ventilation matters more than with lighter shingles.",
      "CertainTeed mixes a small percentage of charcoal-toned granules into the blend to give the surface visual texture without lifting the perceived color. In overcast Florida humidity, that texture is what separates a $4,000 asphalt roof from a $40,000 metal one in photos.",
      "Pairs cleanly with white, off-white, navy, deep green, sage, and warm wood siding. It is the safest color in the catalog if you have not committed to a paint palette yet."
    ],
